German Law to Cap Insurance Commissions, Tagesspiegel Says

-- B y   R i c h a r d   W e i s s
-- 
2011-10-16T13:34:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-16/german-law-to-cap-insurance-commissions-tagesspiegel-says.html
Germany  aims to cap commissions
brokers collect from insurers for new clients to better protect
consumers and prohibit “excessive” payments,  Tagesspiegel 
newspaper reported, citing a draft of the law it obtained.  To contact the reporter on this story:
